payload.contentString: {"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"delivery","info_text":"Parting with friends is a sadness. A place is only a place."}
{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"delivery","info_text":"Let us not rail about justice as long as we have arms and the freedom to use them."}
{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"delivery","info_text":"But I can tell you, dear God, for the father, nothing."}
{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"delivery","info_text":"A dead man, surely, no longer requires that water."}
{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"delivery","info_text":"A beginning is the time for taking the most delicate care that the balances are correct."}

{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"shipment","info_text":"When your opponent fears you, then's the moment when you give the fear its own rein, give it the time to work on him. Let it become terror. The terrified man fights himself. Eventually, he attacks in desperation. That is the most dangerous moment, but the terrified man can be trusted usually to make a fatal mistake."}
{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"delivery","info_text":"A popular man arouses the jealousy of the powerful."}

{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"delivery","info_text":"The Guild... they're fighting me in the mental vaults. They're behind everything. They fear the one who will come, who will know more, who will see more. The Guild is behind everything. It's not finished yet. I'm not formed."}
{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"shipment","info_text":"Bring in that floating fat man, the Baron!"}

{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"onPremise","info_text":"To attempt an understanding of Muad'Dib without understanding his mortal enemies, the Harkonnens, is to attempt seeing Truth without knowing Falsehood. It is the attempt to see the Light without knowing Darkness. It cannot be."}
{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"onPremise","info_text":"Vendetta, he says, using the ancient tongue. The art of kanly is still alive in the Universe. He does not wish to meet or speak with you."}
{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"delivery","info_text":"To save one from a mistake is a gift of paradise."}

{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"delivery","info_text":"My lord, I suspect an incredible secret has been kept on this planet: that the Fremen exist in vast numbers - vast. And it is they who control Arrakis."}

{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"shipment","info_text":"To attempt an understanding of Muad'Dib without understanding his mortal enemies, the Harkonnens, is to attempt seeing Truth without knowing Falsehood. It is the attempt to see the Light without knowing Darkness. It cannot be."}

{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"onPremise","info_text":"Mood? What has mood to do with it? You fight when the necessity arises  no matter the mood! Mood's a thing for cattle or making love or playing the baliset. It's not for fighting."}
{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"shipment","info_text":"You dare suggest a Duke's son is an animal?"}

{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"delivery","info_text":"Those are date palms. One date palm requires forty liters of water a day. A man requires but eight liters. A palm, then, equals five men. There are twenty palms out thereone hundred men."}
{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"delivery","info_text":"Usul has called a big one. Again, it is the legend."}
{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"shipment","info_text":"Many machines on Ix. New machines, better than those on Richesse."}

{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"delivery","info_text":"To attempt an understanding of Muad'Dib without understanding his mortal enemies, the Harkonnens, is to attempt seeing Truth without knowing Falsehood. It is the attempt to see the Light without knowing Darkness. It cannot be."}
{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"shipment","info_text":"A popular man arouses the jealousy of the powerful."}
{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"delivery","info_text":"What delicious abandon in the sleep of the child. Where do we lose it?"}

{"version":1,"supplyOptionsType":"delivery","info_text":"Men and their works have been a disease on the surface of their planets before now. Nature tends to compensate for diseases, to remove or encapsulate them, to incorporate them into the system in her own way."}
